<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL 9, 10, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - TROUBLESHOOTING NOISES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING NOISES</title>
        <para>For all noise conditions, check the following before disassembling the transmission:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check that the oil level is even with the bottom of the fill plug hole.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the correct oil is used.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the driveline angles of the transmission are correct.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the transmission is correctly installed.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drain plug. Check for any metal shavings, gasket material or any other material
                in the oil.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <para>In some noise conditions, there are additional repairs to perform. These repairs will be explained in the
            following tables.
        </para>
        <table id="x1303307">
            <title>Troubleshooting Noises</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.46in"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.52in"/>
                <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.47in"/>
                <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Condition</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Possible Cause</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Remedy</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1" morerows="2">
                            <para>Growling, humming or grinding*</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>1. Worn or damaged gears.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>1. Replace gears.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>2. Worn bearings (humming only).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>2. Replace bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>3. End play out of specifications.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>3. Check and adjust end play.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1" morerows="1">
                            <para>Hissing, thumping or bumping**</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>1. Damaged bearings (hissing only).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>1. Replace bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>2. Damaged gear teeth (thumping or bumping only.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>2. Replace gears.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1" morerows="5">
                            <para>Rattles</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>1. Engine idle speed not within specifications.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>1. Adjust idle speed to specified RPM.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>2. Engine does not operate on all cylinders.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>2. Adjust or repair engine.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>3. Clutch intermediate or center plate binding in housing.***</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>3. Repair or replace intermediate or center plate.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>4. Other systems.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>4. Make sure the transmission is the source of the rattle condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>5. Incorrect shim installation on the PTO unit.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>5. Install correct shims on PTO unit.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>6. Damaged washers between mainshaft gears.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>6. Replace washers between mainshaft gears.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1" morerows="2">
                            <para>Squealing or whining****</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>1. Incorrect shim installation on PTO unit.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>1. Install correct shims on PTO unit.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>2. Damaged bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>2. Replace bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>3. End play of countershafts not within specifications.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>3. Adjust countershaft end play within specifications.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                            <para>*Growling and humming are associated with the first stages of the condition. Grinding
                                is associated with the severe stages of the condition.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                            <para>**Hissing is associated with the first stages of the condition. Thumping and bumping
                                are associated with the severe stages of the condition.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                            <para>***If the noise occurs when the clutch is engaged and stops when the clutch is
                                disengaged, the intermediate or center plate is the cause of the rattle.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                            <para>****Whining is a medium pitched noise. Squealing is a high pitched noise.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
